<item>
  <title>ICCB 2025</title>
  <link>https://ThomasLavigne.github.io/posts/2025/2025-09-10-ICCB/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>This week, my co-authors <a href="https://m3disim.saclay.inria.fr/people/katerina-skardova">Kateřina Škardová</a> and <a href="https://mgenet.github.io/">Martin Genet</a>, my collegues Jean-Marc Allain, Felipe Álvarez-Barrientos, Haotian Xiao, and Julien Bonnafé, and I attended the <a href="https://iccb2025.org/">2025 ICCB</a> conference. <a href="https://m3disim.saclay.inria.fr/people/katerina-skardova">Kateřina Škardová</a> and I both presented our work towards getting a real-time digital twin of the lungs <span class="citation" data-cites="daby-seesaramFiniteElementNeural2025 skardovaFiniteElementNeural2025">(<strong>daby-seesaramFiniteElementNeural2025?</strong>; <strong>skardovaFiniteElementNeural2025?</strong>)</span>.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, <a href="https://mgenet.github.io/">Martin Genet</a> chaired the mini-symposium “<strong>MS08 - 1: Modeling the respiratory system: current trends and clinical opportunities</strong>” he co-organised.</p>
