<item>
  <title>Invited speaker at the RICAM of the Austrian Academy of Sciences</title>
  <link>https://ThomasLavigne.github.io/posts/2024/2024-10-22-RICAM/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>Today I was invited to give a seminar at the Johann Radon Institute for Computational and Applied Mathematics (<a href="https://www.oeaw.ac.at/ricam/">RICAM</a>) of the Austrian Academy of Sciences, in the Computational Methods for PDEs group. I had the opportunity to present our work on reduced-order modelling and recent hybridisation of the PGD with the Finite Element Neural Network Interpolation (FENNI) framework <span class="citation" data-cites="daby-seesaramFiniteElementNeural2024 skardovaFiniteElementNeural2024">(<strong>daby-seesaramFiniteElementNeural2024?</strong>; <strong>skardovaFiniteElementNeural2024?</strong>)</span>.</p>
<p>The shown exemples used our open-source code, <a href="https://pypi.org/project/NeuROM-Py/">NeuROM</a></p>
